 humiliate, and financially ruin wealthy and powerful men. In pursuing their desires, the putains challenge contemporary notions of womanhood and expose the injustices of ancien-régime France. Until the French Revolution spelled the end of the genre, these novels proposed not only an appealing libertine utopia in which libertine women enjoy the same benefits as their male counterparts but also entirely new ways of looking at systems of power, gender, and sexuality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAutobiographical fiction, FrenchxHistory and criticism. 0aFrench fictiony18th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aLibertines in literature. 0aProstitutes in literature. 0aWomen in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aLa Belle Allemande, Margot la ravaudeuse, La Cauchoise, Histoire de Juliette, Juliette, Sade, gender studies, women's studies, eighteenth-century studies, eighteenth-century France, French studies, French history, literary studies, pre-revolutionary France, ancien-régime France, French literature, libertine literature, memoir novel, sexuality, sex work, eighteenth-century prostitute, female libertines, putain, putains, female friendship, feminine networks.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z978311131826440uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978164453326040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644533260423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781644533260/original  a978-3-11-131826-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 202